subSubSection.paragraph:
Head
. Antenna with 84 antennomeres; apical flagellomere slightly acute, 2.4 × longer than its maximum width; penultimate flagellomere 1.6 × longer than its maximum width, and 0.7 × as long as apical flagellomere; median flagellomeres 1.3 × longer than its width; first flagellomere 1.2 and 1.4 × longer than second and third, respectively, the latter being 1.2 × longer than wide; scapus 1.6 × longer than its apically width (
Fig. 42l
); malar suture with some short setae and weak punctures (

Fig. 
42g

); tentorio-ocular distance: inter-tentorial distance: maximum width across mandibles = 1.0: 1.8: 3.1; clypeus with sparse long setae; eye weakly emarginated (

Fig. 
42g

); face sparsely punctate, and with dense short setae laterally (

Fig. 
42g

); face width: head width: eye height = 1.0: 1.8: 0.85; frons smooth, weakly concave behind antennal sockets, median groove indistinct (
Fig. 42h
); vertex smooth, with sparse short setae; shortest distance between posterior ocellus and eye: distance between median ocellus and antennal socket: width of head behind eyes (occiput) = 1.0: 0.7: 4.1; temples subparallel-sided behind eyes (
Fig. 42h
).

Mesosoma
. Length of mesosoma 1.8 × its height (
Fig. 42c
); notauli only impressed anteriorly (
Fig. 42d
); mesoscutum smooth and sparsely short setose (
Fig. 42d
); scutellar sulcus deep, moderately narrow, with crenulae (
Fig. 42d
); scutellum smooth, with dense short setae posteriorly; metanotum moderately convex medially (
Fig. 42d
); propodeum largely smooth, without medio-longitudinal carina or groove, and sparsely setose medially, with dense long setae laterally (
Fig. 42j
).

Wings
. Fore wing (
Fig. 42a
): second submarginal cell rather long; SR1: 3-SR: r = 3.1: 2.2: 1.0; 1-SR+M weakly curved posteriorly towards anterior wing margin, 1.5 × longer than 1-M; 2-SR: 3-SR: r-m = 1.2: 2.3: 1.0; m-cu straight, 3.8 × longer than 2-SR+M. Hind wing (
Fig. 42b
): 1r-m more or less straight, 0.8 × longer than SC+R1.

Metasoma
. Length of first tergite 1.3 × its apical width, concave medio-basally, median area convex and ovoid, smooth anteriorly, sculptured posteriorly (
Fig. 42k
); first tergite without lateral carina, lateral grooves narrow and crenulate (
Fig. 42k
); apical width of second tergite 1.4 × its medial length; triangular medio-basal area of second tergite large and smooth; antero-lateral areas of second tergite large and smooth, oblique anterior grooves narrow and weakly crenulate posteriorly; second tergite largely rugose except for medio-basal and antero-lateral areas (
Fig. 42e
); second suture deep, crenulate, more or less straight medially (
Fig. 42e
); apical width of third tergite 2.4 × its medial length; antero-lateral areas of third tergite convex; antero-lateral grooves of third tergite largely deep, weakly crenulate and joining medially; antero-lateral areas of fourth tergite large (
Fig. 42e
); third–fourth tergites largely rugose except for antero-lateral areas and posteriorly, and with transverse subposterior grooves (of third tergite crenulate, but of fourth tergite largely smooth); fifth–seventh tergites smooth (
Fig. 42e
); hypopygium acute apically, reaching far beyond level of apex of metasoma; ovipositor sheath 2.1 × longer than fore wing.

Colour
. Largely yellow (
Fig. 41
); antenna, mandible apically, stemmaticum and ovipositor sheaths black, and with a black spot on either side of lateral ocellus, middle lobe of mesoscutum and lateral lobes anteriorly somewhat infuscate (
Figs 41
, 

42d, 
42g
, 42h

); middle and hind tibia apically, fore and middle tarsi yellowish brown, claws, and hind tarsus dark brown (
Fig. 42f
); fifth and sixth metasomal tergites black (but sixth tergite laterally yellow) (
Fig. 42e
); wing membrane largely smoky grey, fore wing with two pale longitudinal areas medially and subapically, and with a dark brown stigmal spot up to vein 1-SR+M, and a dark brown spot in marginal cell anteriorly; pterostigma basally yellow and apically dark brown, and veins dark brown (
Figs 42a, 42b
).
